verses.text_plain: Then Nahash the Ammonite came up, and encamped against Jabesh–gilead: and all the men of Jabesh said unto Nahash, Make a covenant with us, and we will serve thee.
verses.verse_html: 1Then Nahash the Ammonite came up, and encamped against Jabesh–gilead: and all the men of Jabesh said unto Nahash, Make a covenant with us, and we will serve thee.

tokens.text: with us, and we will serve

verses.text_plain: And Nahash the Ammonite answered them, On this condition will I make a covenant with you, that I may thrust out all your right eyes, and lay it for a reproach upon all Israel.
verses.verse_html: 2And Nahash the Ammonite answered them, On this condition will I make a covenant with you, that I may thrust out all your right eyes, and lay it for a reproach upon all Israel.

tokens.text: with you, that I may thrust out

verses.text_plain: And the elders of Jabesh said unto him, Give us seven days’ respite, that we may send messengers unto all the coasts of Israel: and then, if there be no man to save us, we will come out to thee.
verses.verse_html:
3And the elders of Jabesh said unto him, Give us seven days’ respite, that we may send messengers unto all the coasts of Israel: and then, if there be no man to save us, we will come out to thee. ▼
▼ Give…: Heb. Forbear us

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Give…: Heb. Forbear us

verses.text_plain: Then came the messengers to Gibeah of Saul, and told the tidings in the ears of the people: and all the people lifted up their voices, and wept.
verses.verse_html: 4Then came the messengers to Gibeah of Saul, and told the tidings in the ears of the people: and all the people lifted up their voices, and wept.

verses.text_plain: And, behold, Saul came after the herd out of the field; and Saul said, What aileth the people that they weep? And they told him the tidings of the men of Jabesh.
verses.verse_html: 5And, behold, Saul came after the herd out of the field; and Saul said, What aileth the people that they weep? And they told him the tidings of the men of Jabesh.

verses.text_plain: And the Spirit of God came upon Saul when he heard those tidings, and his anger was kindled greatly.
verses.verse_html: 6And the Spirit of God came upon Saul when he heard those tidings, and his anger was kindled greatly.

verses.text_plain: And he took a yoke of oxen, and hewed them in pieces, and sent them throughout all the coasts of Israel by the hands of messengers, saying, Whosoever cometh not forth after Saul and after Samuel, so shall it be done unto his oxen. And the fear of the Lord fell on the people, and they came out with one consent.
verses.verse_html:
7And he took a yoke of oxen, and hewed them in pieces, and sent them throughout all the coasts of Israel by the hands of messengers, saying, Whosoever cometh not forth after Saul and after Samuel, so shall it be done unto his oxen. And the fear of the Lord fell on the people, and they came out with one consent. ▼
▼ with…: Heb. as one man

footnotes.body_html: ▼ with…: Heb. as one man

verses.text_plain: And when he numbered them in Bezek, the children of Israel were three hundred thousand, and the men of Judah thirty thousand.
verses.verse_html: 8And when he numbered them in Bezek, the children of Israel were three hundred thousand, and the men of Judah thirty thousand.

verses.text_plain: And they said unto the messengers that came, Thus shall ye say unto the men of Jabesh–gilead, To morrow, by that time the sun be hot, ye shall have help. And the messengers came and shewed it to the men of Jabesh; and they were glad.
verses.verse_html:
9And they said unto the messengers that came, Thus shall ye say unto the men of Jabesh–gilead, To morrow, by that time the sun be hot, ye shall have help. And the messengers came and shewed it to the men of Jabesh; and they were glad. ▼
▼ help: or, deliverance

verses.text_plain: Therefore the men of Jabesh said, To morrow we will come out unto you, and ye shall do with us all that seemeth good unto you.
verses.verse_html: 10Therefore the men of Jabesh said, To morrow we will come out unto you, and ye shall do with us all that seemeth good unto you.

tokens.text: unto you, and ye shall do

verses.text_plain: And it was so on the morrow, that Saul put the people in three companies; and they came into the midst of the host in the morning watch, and slew the Ammonites until the heat of the day: and it came to pass, that they which remained were scattered, so that two of them were not left together.
verses.verse_html: 11And it was so on the morrow, that Saul put the people in three companies; and they came into the midst of the host in the morning watch, and slew the Ammonites until the heat of the day: and it came to pass, that they which remained were scattered, so that two of them were not left together.

tokens.text: and it came to pass, that they which remained

verses.text_plain: And the people said unto Samuel, Who is he that said, Shall Saul reign over us? bring the men, that we may put them to death.
verses.verse_html: 12And the people said unto Samuel, Who is he that said, Shall Saul reign over us? bring the men, that we may put them to death.

tokens.text: that we may put them to death

verses.text_plain: And Saul said, There shall not a man be put to death this day: for to day the Lord hath wrought salvation in Israel.
verses.verse_html: 13And Saul said, There shall not a man be put to death this day: for to day the Lord hath wrought salvation in Israel.

verses.text_plain: Then said Samuel to the people, Come, and let us go to Gilgal, and renew the kingdom there.
verses.verse_html: 14Then said Samuel to the people, Come, and let us go to Gilgal, and renew the kingdom there.

verses.text_plain: And all the people went to Gilgal; and there they made Saul king before the Lord in Gilgal; and there they sacrificed sacrifices of peace offerings before the Lord; and there Saul and all the men of Israel rejoiced greatly.
verses.verse_html: 15And all the people went to Gilgal; and there they made Saul king before the Lord in Gilgal; and there they sacrificed sacrifices of peace offerings before the Lord; and there Saul and all the men of Israel rejoiced greatly.
